main.name: Jasmine Zhang
main.description: Passionate about learning technology and sharing knowledge
main.bio: I’m Jasmine,an IT student at UWA with a passion for software engineering.My academic journey has been an exciting exploration of web development,programming,cybersecurity and data analysis.Every project and course has fueled my enthusiasm for creating innovative tech solutions.Besides,I dive into extracurricular activities that sharpen my communication and teamwork skills.I’m eager to connect with professionals in the tech industry,seek mentorship,and find internship opportunities to apply my skills in real-world scenarios.

experience.title: International Student Engagement Ambassador
experience.description: Helping international students as they settle into life in Perth.Supporting new students in various aspects and make their transition smooth and enjoyable.Event assisting during orientation week and throughout the semester.Acting as a positive role model and ambassador for UWA.

experience.title: Uni Mentor
experience.description: Supporting new students before and during the semester.Providing mentees information about UWA’s services. Maintaining contact and be responsive to mentees requests for support.

experience.title: Tutor
experience.description: Mentor high school girls by offering hands-on guidance during workshops,adeptly identifying and resolving syntax errors.Enhancing participants' coding proficiency and confidence in problem-solving.
